    {
      "name": "Packages",
      "description": "Upload, list, and read packages.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Upload package — POST /v1/packages",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Idempotency-Key",
                "value": "{{$guid}}",
                "description": "Required. Replaying a request with the same key returns the original operation and does no work twice. Reusing a key for a different request is a 409."
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Your .forge archive. Build one with: python3 scripts/forge_pack.py examples/hello-model"
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["v1", "packages"] },
            "description": "**Stream a .forge archive and validate it.**\n\n⚠️ **You must attach a file.** Postman cannot persist a file path in an exported collection, so open the *Body* tab and select your `.forge` file for the `file` field. Build one first:\n\n```\npython3 scripts/forge_pack.py examples/hello-model\n```\n\n**Returns 202 and an *operation*, not a package** (ADR-006). The `Location` header points at the operation. This test script saves `operationId` and `packageId` into the environment for you.\n\n**A rejected package still returns a *succeeded* operation.** The validation ran; the verdict is on the package. Read the package to see `validation_findings`. An operation only *fails* when the platform could not do the work (for example an unreadable artifact).\n\n**Responses**\n- `202` — operation created (and, today, already completed: validation runs inline).\n- `400 idempotency_key_required` — you omitted the header.\n- `409 idempotency_conflict` — you reused a key for a different request.\n- `422 archive_too_large` — the archive exceeds `FORGEML_PACKAGE_MAX_ARCHIVE_BYTES`.\n- `503 dependency_unavailable` — PostgreSQL is down."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "202 Accepted — validated",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "demo-key-1" }], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages" } },
              "status": "Accepted",
              "code": 202,
              "header": [
                { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
                { "key": "Location", "value": "/v1/operations/bcc62980-3b71-43f4-bead-9eb35622d454" }
              ],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"bcc62980-3b71-43f4-bead-9eb35622d454\",\n  \"type\": \"package_validate\",\n  \"target\": \"385952d3476e770eeba21943c7f041d51ce8e90a93de0d862835540403731c31\",\n  \"state\": \"succeeded\",\n  \"correlation_id\": \"2fa6515d-1523-4a1b-90bd-862ff9885c41\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"package_id\": \"7be9afb4-3344-41cb-80a1-02d43b2e91ce\",\n    \"validation_state\": \"validated\"\n  },\n  \"failure\": null,\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:17:28.069603Z\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:17:28.096915Z\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:17:28.102517Z\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "202 Accepted — package rejected",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "broken-1" }], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages" } },
              "status": "Accepted",
              "code": 202,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"a1c2e3d4-0000-4000-8000-000000000001\",\n  \"type\": \"package_validate\",\n  \"target\": \"9f2c...\",\n  \"state\": \"succeeded\",\n  \"correlation_id\": \"11111111-2222-4333-8444-555555555555\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"package_id\": \"c940ea06-961c-4c84-bb5f-95d8e5d6a7df\",\n    \"validation_state\": \"rejected\"\n  },\n  \"failure\": null,\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:19:02.000000Z\",\n  \"updated_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:19:02.010000Z\",\n  \"completed_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:19:02.012000Z\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "400 Idempotency-Key required",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "POST", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages" } },
              "status": "Bad Request",
              "code": 400,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"code\": \"idempotency_key_required\",\n  \"message\": \"An Idempotency-Key header is required.\",\n  \"request_id\": \"83b5f3ea-2e09-4733-ad6a-4995f353a989\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "409 Idempotency conflict",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Idempotency-Key", "value": "demo-key-1" }], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages" } },
              "status": "Conflict",
              "code": 409,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"code\": \"idempotency_conflict\",\n  \"message\": \"this idempotency key was already used for a different request\",\n  \"request_id\": \"d02e6501-f4ea-43a9-9d5c-fbca8fb21e80\"\n}"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 400) {",
                  "    pm.test('400 means you did not attach an Idempotency-Key', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('idempotency_key_required');",
                  "    });",
                  "    return;",
                  "}",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('202 Accepted (a long-running command returns an operation)', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.status(202);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Location points at the operation', function () {",
                  "    pm.response.to.have.header('Location');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "const operation = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('It is an operation resource, not a package', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(operation).to.have.property('state');",
                  "    pm.expect(operation.type).to.eql('package_validate');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('The target is the archive checksum (ADR-003)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(operation.target).to.match(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('correlation_id equals the response X-Request-ID (ADR-015)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(operation.correlation_id).to.eql(pm.response.headers.get('X-Request-ID'));",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "// Extract the variables the rest of the collection needs.",
                  "pm.environment.set('operationId', operation.id);",
                  "if (operation.result && operation.result.package_id) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('packageId', operation.result.package_id);",
                  "    console.log('validation_state =', operation.result.validation_state);",
                  "}",
                  "pm.environment.set('correlationId', operation.correlation_id);",
                  "",
                  "if (operation.state === 'failed') {",
                  "    console.warn('The operation FAILED. That is a platform fault, not a bad package:', JSON.stringify(operation.failure));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Read package — GET /v1/packages/{id}",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages/{{packageId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "packages", "{{packageId}}"]
            },
            "description": "**Read one package, with its manifest and validation findings.**\n\nThis is where the *verdict* lives. `validation_state` is `validated` or `rejected`; when rejected, `validation_findings` lists stable machine codes with a logical path (for example `dependency_not_pinned` at `[\"dependencies\", 0]`).\n\n`manifest` is populated only for a validated package — the platform will not report a manifest it did not accept. `manifest_version` is `null` until validation has actually parsed the archive.\n\n`{{packageId}}` is set automatically by the Upload request.\n\n**404 `package_not_found`** — unknown id.\n**422** — the id is not a UUID."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — validated",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "GET", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages/{{packageId}}" } },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"7be9afb4-3344-41cb-80a1-02d43b2e91ce\",\n  \"sha256\": \"385952d3476e770eeba21943c7f041d51ce8e90a93de0d862835540403731c31\",\n  \"filename\": \"hello-model.forge\",\n  \"size_bytes\": 1057,\n  \"manifest_version\": 1,\n  \"validation_state\": \"validated\",\n  \"validation_findings\": null,\n  \"manifest\": {\n    \"forge_version\": 1,\n    \"model\": { \"name\": \"Hello Model\", \"framework\": \"python-callable\", \"version\": \"1.0.0\" },\n    \"runtime\": { \"python\": \"3.11\" },\n    \"entrypoint\": { \"module\": \"model\", \"callable\": \"predict\" }\n  },\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:17:28.069603Z\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "200 OK — rejected, with findings",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "GET", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages/{{packageId}}" } },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"id\": \"c940ea06-961c-4c84-bb5f-95d8e5d6a7df\",\n  \"sha256\": \"9f2c...\",\n  \"filename\": \"broken.forge\",\n  \"size_bytes\": 1063,\n  \"manifest_version\": null,\n  \"validation_state\": \"rejected\",\n  \"validation_findings\": [\n    {\n      \"code\": \"dependency_not_pinned\",\n      \"message\": \"dependency must be an exact name==version pin\",\n      \"path\": [\"dependencies\", 0]\n    }\n  ],\n  \"manifest\": null,\n  \"created_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:19:02.000000Z\"\n}"
            },
            {
              "name": "404 Not found",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "GET", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages/{{packageId}}" } },
              "status": "Not Found",
              "code": 404,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"code\": \"package_not_found\",\n  \"message\": \"the referenced package does not exist\",\n  \"request_id\": \"7c2b1a90-0000-4000-8000-000000000000\"\n}"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const pkg = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Identity is the SHA-256 of the bytes (ADR-003)', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pkg.sha256).to.match(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Carries a terminal validation verdict', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(pkg.validation_state).to.be.oneOf(['validated', 'rejected']);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (pkg.validation_state === 'validated') {",
                  "    pm.test('A validated package exposes its manifest', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.manifest).to.not.eql(null);",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.manifest.forge_version).to.eql(1);",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.manifest.model.framework).to.eql('python-callable');",
                  "    });",
                  "    pm.test('A validated package has no findings', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.validation_findings).to.eql(null);",
                  "    });",
                  "    pm.test('manifest_version is set once the archive was parsed', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.manifest_version).to.eql(1);",
                  "    });",
                  "} else {",
                  "    pm.test('A rejected package explains itself with stable codes', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.validation_findings).to.be.an('array').that.is.not.empty;",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.validation_findings[0]).to.have.property('code');",
                  "        pm.expect(pkg.validation_findings[0]).to.have.property('message');",
                  "    });",
                  "    console.log('Findings:', pkg.validation_findings.map(f => f.code).join(', '));",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List packages — GET /v1/packages",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages?limit=50",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "packages"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50", "description": "1–100. Default 50. Outside that range is a 422." },
                { "key": "cursor", "value": "", "description": "Opaque cursor from a previous page's next_cursor. Disabled by default.", "disabled": true }
              ]
            },
            "description": "**List packages, newest first.**\n\nKeyset pagination: pass the previous response's `next_cursor` back as `cursor`. The cursor is **opaque** — do not construct one by hand; it encodes internal ordering keys and its format is not a contract. `next_cursor` is `null` on the last page.\n\n**422** — `limit` outside 1–100.\n**400 `cursor_invalid`** — a cursor we did not issue."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "GET", "header": [], "url": { "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/packages?limit=50" } },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
              "body": "{\n  \"items\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"7be9afb4-3344-41cb-80a1-02d43b2e91ce\",\n      \"sha256\": \"385952d3476e770eeba21943c7f041d51ce8e90a93de0d862835540403731c31\",\n      \"filename\": \"hello-model.forge\",\n      \"size_bytes\": 1057,\n      \"validation_state\": \"validated\",\n      \"created_at\": \"2026-07-14T20:17:28.069603Z\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"next_cursor\": null\n}"
            }
          ],
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('200 OK', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const page = pm.response.json();",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Returns a page', function () {",
                  "    pm.expect(page.items).to.be.an('array');",
                  "    pm.expect(page).to.have.property('next_cursor');",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "pm.test('Ordered newest first', function () {",
                  "    const times = page.items.map(i => Date.parse(i.created_at));",
                  "    const sorted = [...times].sort((a, b) => b - a);",
                  "    pm.expect(times).to.eql(sorted);",
                  "});",
                  "",
                  "if (page.next_cursor) {",
                  "    pm.environment.set('cursor', page.next_cursor);",
                  "    console.log('More pages. Enable the cursor query param and re-send.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Operations",
      "description": "Poll durable operations (ADR-006).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Poll operation — GET /v1/operations/{id}",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/operations/{{operationId}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["v1", "operations", "{{operationId}}"]
            },
            "description": "**Poll a durable operation.**\n\nStates: `pending` → `running` → `succeeded` | `failed`. The terminal states are **immutable** — the database enforces it — so a poll is always truthful.\n\nValidation currently runs inside the upload request, so an operation is usually already `succeeded` by the time you first poll it. That will stay true from the client's point of view when the work moves to a background worker: this contract exists precisely so that change is invisible to you.\n\n- `state: succeeded` → `result.package_id` and `result.validation_state`. **Note that `succeeded` says the validation *ran*, not that the package was accepted.** Read the package for the verdict.\n- `state: failed` → `failure.code` — the platform could not do the work (for example `artifact_unreadable`). This is *not* a bad package.\n\n`{{operationId}}` is set automatically by the Upload request.\n\n**404 `operation_not_found`** — unknown id."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — succeeded",
